agon  (n):

1)A struggle or contest; conflict; especially between the protagonist and antagonist in a literary work. 
2)A test of will; a conflict: “Freud's originality stemmed from his aggression and ambition in his agon with biology” (Harold Bloom). 
4)A contest in ancient Greece, as in athletics or music, in which prizes were awarded. 




n. pl. a·gon·es